/c_01620050120en00010020.pdf\" title=\"Download 'List of bodies or public authorities in charge of inspection provided for in article 15 of regulation (EEC) (PDF, 94KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘List of bodies or public authorities in charge of inspection provided for in article 15 of regulation (EEC)’ (PDF, 94 KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>An organic certification body is an independent organisation that has standards for its members that meet or exceed government regulations.</p>\n\n<h2>Imports from outside the EU</h2>\n\n<p>You can import certain organic products from countries that are covered under &lsquo;equivalence agreements&rsquo; -  this means they have no import restrictions.</p>\n\n<p>The countries that have equivalence agreements with the UK are: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Argentina</li>\n  <li>Australia</li>\n  <li>Costa Rica</li>\n  <li>India</li>\n  <li>Israel</li>\n  <li>Japan</li>\n  <li>New Zealand</li>\n  <li>Switzerland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Not all products will be covered by equivalence agreements. Call the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs (<abbr title=\"Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs\">Defra</abbr>) helpline if you are unsure whether a product is covered by an agreement.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs\">Defra</abbr> Helpline</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>08459 335 577</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>For countries not covered by equivalence agreements, you must: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.defra.gov.uk/forms/2011/03/30/ob11-organic-products/\" title=\"Initial application to market in the EU organic products from third countries\">apply for approval from <abbr title=\"Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs\">Defra</abbr></a> before importing</li>\n  <li>be registered with an EU Organic Certification Body </li>\n  <li>have a Certificate of Inspection for the food you want to import</li>\n</ul>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.go